{{Quote|Good grief! There must be some error. This facility is neutral. Even the Empire, Re-"<br />"Shut up junk!|Beilert Valance destroys a [[Unidentified robot orderly|robot orderly]] during his raid on Anglebay Station|<ref name="marvel16" />}}
'''Anglebay Station''' was a neutral, unaligned medical station located on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] [[Planet/Legends|world]] of [[Telos IV]]. Active during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], Anglebay Station offered its services to those serving both the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] alike during the conflict. During the [[Kwymar Suppressions]] in Telos' [[Kwymar sector|home sector]] in [[17 BBY/Legends|17 BBY]], some Imperial casualties were sent to Anglebay Station, including [[Beilert Valance/Legends|Beilert Valance]], a [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] [[Stormtrooper Commander/Legends|commander]] who was grievously wounded on [[Doniphon]]. On Anglebay Station, Valance was rebuilt with [[Cybernetics/Legends|cybernetic]] parts, ending his military career and pushing him into a life as a [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]]. In [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]], driven near to madness by his hatred of his mechanical state, Valance led an [[Attack on Anglebay Station|attack]] on Anglebay Station that slaughtered everyone in the facility and ultimately completely destroyed the hospital.

==Description==
{{Quote|Wait! This is just the computer record section. There are no drugs... anything of value!|An staff member at Anglebay Station during Beilert Valance's attack|<ref name="marvel16" />}}
An isolated medical station on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Telos IV]], Anglebay Station was known during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] for its neutrality, offering healing services to [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]], and unaligned individuals alike. The station heavily employed [[Droid/Legends|droids]] among its staff, along with a sizable contingent of organic employees. Anglebay Station had a unit of in-patient bays that housed recuperating patients, along with an extensive computer records system that carried information on every patient who passed through the facility.<ref name="marvel16" /> During the early [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Era]], [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] treatment at Anglebay Station was often rationed out based on the patient's rank and prognosis. In cases where a patient wasn't considered priority to receive bacta treatment but had suffered serious injuries, Anglebay Station was known to perform surgeries that infused the subject with [[Cybernetics/Legends|cybernetic]] parts.<ref name="warfare">{{SW|url=news/the-essential-guide-to-warfare-authors-cut-part-11-serving-the-empire|series=Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Warfare Author's Cut|text=Part 11: Serving the Empire}}</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|We're rounding up all the robot orderlies, Captain."<br />"You know what to do, Slssk.|Slssk and Beilert Valance during the attack on Anglebay Station|<ref name="marvel16" />}}
Active during the era of the Galactic Civil War, Anglebay Station offered medical services to people regardless of their affiliation, both Imperials and rebels alike. In [[17 BBY/Legends|17 BBY]], that included a young [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] [[Stormtrooper Commander/Legends|commander]] named [[Beilert Valance/Legends|Beilert Valance]], who suffered grave injuries in an Imperial [[Assault on Doniphon|assault]] on a rebel outpost on [[Doniphon]]. Doniphon was located in the same [[Kwymar sector|sector]] as Telos IV, and Valance was brought to Anglebay Station for treatment. Wounded from a [[Torpedo/Legends|torpedo]] impact, Valance was admitted to Anglebay Station with severe blast and burn damage to his head and torso, and his prognosis was rated poor. As bacta supplies were prioritized for higher-ranking personnel, Valance instead received surgery that rebuilt the damaged parts of his body with cybernetics. Valance awoke over 11 days later, realizing to his horror that he had become a [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborg]]<ref name="warfare" />&mdash;although he recovered to walk out of the hospital some time later, his career in the [[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial Military]] was over.<ref name="marvel16" />

[[File:TheVteam-MSW16.png|thumb|left|250px|Beilert Valance leads the attack on Anglebay Station.]]
Seventeen years later, Valance returned to Anglebay Station a very different man. Despising his own status as a cyborg, the former Imperial officer had become a dangerously unhinged [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] leading a rough-and-tumble crew across the Outer Rim. Valance had hidden his cybernetic replacements ever since his departure from Anglebay Station, and in [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] he decided it was time to destroy the past for good.<ref name="marvel16" /> To achieve this, Valance ordered his crew to attack and completely destroy Anglebay Station, leaving no survivors&mdash;although his men were killers, this act of wanton slaughter gave many of them pause until Valance assured them they would be very well compensated.<ref name="tnms">{{SW|url=news/the-not-so-magnificent-seven|text=The Not-So Magnificent Seven|int=The Not-So Magnificent Seven|nolive=1}}</ref> Once his gang was on-board, Valance led his men in a destructive [[Attack on Anglebay Station|raid]] on Anglebay Station, indiscriminately murdering whoever they came across.<ref name="marvel16" />

While one group of his men focused on killing everyone in the facility, with particular malice reserved towards Anglebay Station's droid population, Valance moved on to his main objective, the station's computer records. Once there, Valance and several of his thugs completely destroyed the station's archives, erasing all trace of his treatment there more than a decade before. Meanwhile, the other group of raiders&mdash;led by Valance's [[Hutlarian]] second-in-command [[Slssk]]&mdash;swept through the in-patient bays, butchering the patients, doctors and staff they found within. However, Slssk and fellow hunter [[Remel Fud]] by chance overheard an interesting piece of information from a senile [[Don-Wan Kihotay|elderly man]] in one of the in-patient bays: the bedridden man's ramblings linked a [[Lepi/Legends|Lepi]] [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] named [[Jaxxon/Legends|Jaxxon]] to wanted Rebel fugitive [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and a mysterious "[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|farmboy]]" who had become Valance's obsession. After reporting this to Valance, the crew sped off to track Jaxxon down, obliterating Anglebay Station with [[proton charge]]s as they departed.<ref name="marvel16" />

==Behind the scenes==
Anglebay Station first appeared in [[Star Wars (1977) 16|''Star Wars'' (1977) 16]], written by [[Archie Goodwin]] and released in [[1978]], although it was unnamed in its original appearance.<ref name="marvel16" /> The station stayed unidentified until [[2004]], when author [[Jason Fry]] gave it the name "Anglebay Station" in the [[Star Wars Miniatures|''Star Wars'' Miniatures]] scenario ''[[The Hunt Within: Valance's Tale: Part 2|Mission 2: Destroying the Past]]''.<ref name="valance5">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=swminis/article/huntwithin5|text=The Hunt Within: Valance's Tale: Conclusion|int=The Hunt Within: Valance's Tale: Conclusion}}</ref>

